Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: chime
Version: 1.0.0
Summary: Set alarms and reminders from GNOME Terminal
Home-page: https://github.com/vlahm/chime
Author: Mike Vlah
Author-email: vlahm13@gmail.com
License: GPL-3
Description: Open a terminal window and call chime with the
            number of hours, minutes, and/or seconds to wait before it dings.
            Optionally, set a reminder message.  The program can be made to work even
            if you close its terminal, though it will be cancelled if you log off or
            shut down your computer.
Keywords: desktop,tools,utility,timer
Platform: UNKNOWN
Classifier: Development Status :: 3 - Alpha
Classifier: Environment :: X11 Applications :: Gnome
Classifier: Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop
Classifier: Framework :: Setuptools Plugin
Classifier: Topic :: Desktop Environment :: Gnome
Classifier: License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)
Classifier: Natural Language :: English
Classifier: Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux
Classifier: Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7
